commit.message:
Small doc updates, clarify references to "snapraid touch". (#19)

Co-authored-by: Andrea Mazzoleni <amadvance@gmail.com>
Fix integer overflow when computing the progress percentage

Fix error when configuring a contentfile in / (#18)

When using this config line:
content /snapraid.content
SnapRAID throws this error:
Error accessing 'content' dir '' specification in '/etc/snapraid.conf' at line 17

This commit fixes that by not replacing the rightmost slash with NUL but
instead the char immediately after the slash.

commit.message: Update address of FSF in GPLv2
Use dd instead of head to be compatible with OpenBSD

Fix build issue with GLIBC 2.36

The sys/mount.h and linux/mount.h (included by linux/fs.h) are incompatible
in glibc 2.36 as both declare fsconfig_command.
Anyway, sys/mount.h is needed only in darwin for statfs and we can avoid to
include it in linux.
Fix build errors with new mingw compiler
Increase default disk cache to 16 MiB

Remove all scan buffers from the stack

This reduces even more the stack utilization.

Reduce stack allocation in dir scanning

This allow to work in environments with low stack size, like MUSL that has only 128K.
Add the option --test-skip-multi-scan to skip multithreads scan
